This paper is about deep learning-based single image super-resolution, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new network architecture that uses multiple HourGlass modules and back projection blocks, which are techniques commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of Softmax-based weighted reconstruction, which is a technique used in machine learning (cs.AI). The paper presents experimental results on various datasets, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses deep neural networks to improve super-resolution, which is a topic related to neural networks (cs.NE).
